1. General Corporate / Office Words

Stakeholder
English: A person/group with interest in a project or company
Hindi: वह व्यक्ति या समूह जिसका प्रोजेक्ट या कंपनी में हित हो

Deliverable
English: Final output to be submitted
Hindi: सौंपे जाने वाला अंतिम परिणाम

Deadline
English: Last date to finish work
Hindi: काम पूरा करने की अंतिम तारीख

Bandwidth
English: Available capacity or time
Hindi: उपलब्ध समय या क्षमता

Alignment
English: Agreement or synchronization
Hindi: तालमेल या सहमति

Escalation
English: Raising an issue to higher authority
Hindi: समस्या को उच्च अधिकारी तक ले जाना

Ownership
English: Responsibility for a task
Hindi: जिम्मेदारी लेना

Action Item
English: Task that needs to be done
Hindi: किया जाने वाला कार्य

Follow-up
English: Checking progress later
Hindi: बाद में स्थिति की जाँच

Meeting Minutes (MoM)
English: Summary of meeting discussion
Hindi: मीटिंग का संक्षेप विवरण

2. IT / Software Development Terms

Requirement Gathering
English: Collecting client needs
Hindi: क्लाइंट की आवश्यकताएँ समझना

Implementation
English: Converting plan into code
Hindi: योजना को कोड में लागू करना

Deployment
English: Releasing software to production
Hindi: सॉफ्टवेयर को लाइव करना

Production (Prod)
English: Live environment
Hindi: वास्तविक उपयोग का वातावरण

Staging
English: Testing environment before production
Hindi: लाइव से पहले परीक्षण वातावरण

Bug
English: Error in software
Hindi: सॉफ्टवेयर की गलती

Fix
English: Solution to a bug
Hindi: गलती का समाधान

Patch
English: Small update to fix issues
Hindi: छोटी सुधार अपडेट

Code Review
English: Checking code quality
Hindi: कोड की समीक्षा

Refactoring
English: Improving code without changing logic
Hindi: लॉजिक बदले बिना कोड सुधारना

3. Project Management Words

Sprint
English: Short development cycle
Hindi: छोटा विकास चरण

Backlog
English: List of pending tasks
Hindi: लंबित कार्यों की सूची

Milestone
English: Major project checkpoint
Hindi: प्रोजेक्ट का महत्वपूर्ण चरण

Timeline
English: Project schedule
Hindi: परियोजना की समयरेखा

Scope
English: Work included in project
Hindi: प्रोजेक्ट की सीमा

Scope Creep
English: Unplanned increase in work
Hindi: बिना योजना काम बढ़ जाना

Risk
English: Potential problem
Hindi: संभावित खतरा

Dependency
English: Task dependent on another task
Hindi: दूसरे कार्य पर निर्भरता

Resource Allocation
English: Assigning people/tools
Hindi: संसाधनों का आवंटन

On Track
English: Progressing as planned
Hindi: योजना के अनुसार चल रहा

4. Communication / Email Corporate Words

Looping You In
English: Adding someone to conversation
Hindi: बातचीत में शामिल करना

Touch Base
English: Quick discussion
Hindi: संक्षिप्त बातचीत

FYI (For Your Information)
English: Just for information
Hindi: केवल जानकारी हेतु

ASAP
English: As soon as possible
Hindi: जितनी जल्दी हो सके

Circling Back
English: Returning to topic later
Hindi: बाद में विषय पर वापस आना

Sync Up
English: Align through discussion
Hindi: चर्चा करके तालमेल बनाना

Acknowledged
English: Message received
Hindi: संदेश प्राप्त हुआ

Noted
English: Understood and recorded
Hindi: समझ लिया और नोट कर लिया

Revert Back
English: Respond later
Hindi: बाद में जवाब देना

Heads-up
English: Advance warning
Hindi: पहले से सूचना

5. Performance & Business Words

KPI (Key Performance Indicator)
English: Performance measurement metric
Hindi: प्रदर्शन मापने का पैमाना

Productivity
English: Efficiency of work
Hindi: कार्य दक्षता

Optimization
English: Improving performance
Hindi: प्रदर्शन सुधार

Revenue
English: Income earned
Hindi: आय

Cost-effective
English: Economical solution
Hindi: कम लागत वाला समाधान

Scalability
English: Ability to handle growth
Hindi: विस्तार की क्षमता

ROI (Return on Investment)
English: Profit from investment
Hindi: निवेश पर लाभ

Benchmark
English: Standard for comparison
Hindi: तुलना का मानक

Best Practices
English: Recommended methods
Hindi: सर्वोत्तम तरीके

Value Addition
English: Extra benefit provided
Hindi: अतिरिक्त लाभ

6. Common Corporate Phrases (Very Important)

Let’s take this offline
English: Discuss privately later
Hindi: बाद में व्यक्तिगत रूप से बात करेंगे

Low-hanging fruit
English: Easy task with quick result
Hindi: आसानी से होने वाला काम

End-to-end
English: From start to finish
Hindi: शुरू से अंत तक

At the earliest
English: As soon as possible
Hindi: सबसे जल्दी संभव

Single point of contact (SPOC)
English: One responsible person
Hindi: एक जिम्मेदार संपर्क व्यक्ति   

Jump the shark.
If a business or product is past its
prime and grasping at straws to stay
relevant, it has jumped the shark.
The metaphor is past its prime;
grasping at this straw makes your
writing suck.
